                            <comment id="16611027" author="githubbot" created="Tue, 11 Sep 2018 18:00:35 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;vrlgohel opened a new pull request #2517: &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CAMEL-12785&quot; title=&quot;ServletComponent ignores httpBinding option&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CAMEL-12785&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CAMEL-12785&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;: ServletComponent ignores HttpBinding&lt;br/&gt;
URL: &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/camel/pull/2517&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/camel/pull/2517&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;p&gt;   We dropped the *&lt;b&gt;httpBindingRef&lt;/b&gt;* in http common and servlet component some time back. The Servlet Component had a regression where it wasn&apos;t taking into consideration a custom *&lt;b&gt;httpBinding&lt;/b&gt;&lt;b&gt;, and instead always initialized a default instance of **ServletRestHttpBinding&lt;/b&gt;*, thereby ignoring the custom config. &lt;br/&gt;
   This change now takes into effect *&lt;b&gt;user&apos;s custom httpBinding&lt;/b&gt;*. &lt;/p&gt;

